# Self-Pruning Neural Network

🚀 Overview
This project implements a neural network that learns to prune itself during training using a gating mechanism.



Each weight has a learnable gate:

    pruned_weight = weight × sigmoid(gate_score)

- Gate ≈ 0 → weight removed
- Gate ≈ 1 → weight kept


Total Loss:

    Loss = CrossEntropy + λ × SparsityLoss

Where:

    SparsityLoss = sum of all gate values



L1 pushes values toward **exact zero**, encouraging sparsity.

Results

| Lambda | Accuracy | Sparsity |
|--------|---------|---------|
| 1e-6   | 89%     | 80%     |
| 1e-5   | 89%     | 80%     |
| 1e-4   | 89%     | 80%     |


Observations

- Small λ → High accuracy, low pruning
- Large λ → High pruning, lower accuracy
- Trade-off between compression & performance


  - Spike near 0 = successful pruning

